      "comment": "THE VICARS GIRL (6) continued the strong recent form when she scored at Globe Derby on Saturday, working before cruising home by more than 13m. That was her sixth win from her last eight starts so her form is hard to knock. Good enough to overcome the 20m handicap and win again. CAN ADEL SUCCEED (5) turned in yet another strong performance last start when she battled on for third at Globe Derby, making it three placings in a row. Has ground to make up on THE VICARS GIRL through that race but she owns a good record here. GOLDEN SKIES (4) bombed the start in the last outing but won from a standing start the last time she raced at this circuit and distance two back so is a chance with manners. CHICAGO CRAZE (3) can be competitive from the front mark.",
